cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about agreement protocols in distributed systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of different agreement protocols. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is another possibility as the paper evaluates the performance of agreement protocols on a public cloud platform. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions BFT-Smart, a Byzantine fault-tolerant consensus protocol. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also less likely but could be relevant as the paper discusses the performance of agreement protocols in a wide-area network.
